"Page Object Model is a design pattern where each page is represented as a class containing elements and methods. 
Page Factory is a Selenium feature that helps initialize elements 
using @FindBy annotation. Page Factory can be used within POM to make code more readable and maintainable.

--
Main Difference (IMPORTANT)
Feature	Page Factory	Page Object Model
Type	Selenium feature	Design pattern
Purpose	Initialize elements	Structure framework
Uses	@FindBy	Classes for each page
Dependency	Selenium	Independent concept
Code style	Cleaner (less code)	More control

--------------------------
Page Factory is a Selenium class (API)
It helps to initialize web elements using annotations

Example:
@FindBy(id="username")
WebElement username;

@FindBy(id="password")
WebElement password;

public LoginPage(WebDriver driver){
    PageFactory.initElements(driver, this);
}
📌 Key Points:
Uses @FindBy
Reduces driver.findElement()
Clean & readable code
Built-in Selenium feature
